==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plaintive
<hw>Plain"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaintif</ets>. See <er>Plaintiff</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Repining; complaining; lamenting.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressive of sorrow or melancholy; mournful;
sad.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The most <xex>plaintive</xex> ditty.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Landor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Plain"tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Plain"tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plaintless</ent>⟦br⟧
